<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>A significant progress of summarization research relies on an innovative summarization of philosophy, psychology, linguistics, cognitive science, neuroscience, physics, computer science, and artificial intelligence from multiple dimensions.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>However, existing approaches are empirical, mainly relying on statistics, structure and linguistic analysis while neglecting the nature of representation and understanding.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>This paper summarizes previous approaches and explores the fundamental theory and method for summarization from multiple dimensions.</a>
